{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5690733a-9b26-4e6f-ae8f-67475a952c28","content":"No files found in the working directory. I'll provide the solution directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` to enable compiled bindings:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\" ?>\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"Theme\" />\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Notifications\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Font Size\" />\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is adding:\n```xml\nxmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\nx:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**1. Enable warnings-as-errors** for binding failures in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the diagnostic for \"property not found on type specified by x:DataType\".\n\n**2. What this catches:** If you typo a property name (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), the build will emit an error instead of silently failing at runtime.\n\n**3. Optional — treat *all* XAML warnings as errors:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TreatXamlWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatXamlWarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `x:DataType` can also be applied to inner elements (e.g., a `DataTemplate`) if the binding context changes.\n- Use `x:DataType=\"\"` (empty string) to opt out of compiled bindings on a specific subtree when the type isn't known at compile time.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"73fcb049-14d3-4793-a3e8-bd5b6f6716db","outputTokens":591,"requestId":"E84D:203FDB:261457C:2A162B8:69F93E2C"},"id":"c95b0c1b-3a08-4fd8-94c1-7ca03937ec03","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:50.607Z","parentId":"87684b49-0087-4dfa-93e8-5de7a7054be5"}
